parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including instrument cluster failure, speedometer inaccuracy, and reduced engine power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Speedometer and other gauges malfunctioning
reduced engine power
stability system disabled
electrical issues with lights
horn
and other accessories.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate readings of speed, fuel level, and other vital information, leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: Speedometer and other gauges malfunctioning
inaccurate readings
stuck or flickering gauges.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction of engine power can cause the vehicle to slow down or stall, leading to accidents or safety risks, especially on highways.
symptoms: Reduced engine power
stability system disabled
sudden loss of speed
stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines can cause sudden and complete brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaks from the brake lines
and the vehicle may experience a loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of braking power
and the brake pedal may vibrate or pulse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels heavy or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the power steering pump fails
or the steering system makes a grinding or whining noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the steering system makes a clunking or grinding noise
or the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front wheel bearings can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving
the front wheel bearings make a grinding or growling noise
or the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or has excessive play
the steering system makes a clunking or grinding noise
or the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the vehicle loses power.
